What you need to know:

Ben Sutherland, the Editor, BBC Sport Africa said Mboma might "only" have got a silver at Tokyo 2020, but it is her story that clearly resonated with the World Service audience who voted for this award. “A Namibian teenager unheard of before the start of the year, she starts to break through in the early months of 2021 - but in the 400m,” Sutherland said.